{"id":3759,"date":"2025-04-04T12:01:23","date_gmt":"2025-04-04T12:01:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/?p=3759"},"modified":"2025-04-04T12:03:05","modified_gmt":"2025-04-04T12:03:05","slug":"how-heat-pumps-work-a-simple-guide-for-homeowners","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/uncategorized\/how-heat-pumps-work-a-simple-guide-for-homeowners\/","title":{"rendered":"How Heat Pumps Work: A Simple Guide for Homeowners"},"content":{"rendered":"<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-doc-id=\"950237000002286001\" data-doc-type=\"writer\">By Ruth Carol Atieno<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">If you&#8217;ve been looking for an energy-efficient way to keep your home warm in the winter and cool in the summer, you may have come across the term heat pump. But what exactly is a heat pump\u2014and how does it work? In this blog, we&#8217;ll break it down in simple terms, so you can understand how heat pumps provide comfort all year round while saving energy.<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading2\" data-header=\"2\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.94pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.94pt\" data-hd-info=\"2\" data-line-height=\"1.2\"><strong>What Is a Heat Pump\u00a0\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">A heat pump is a device that moves heat from one place to another. It can both heat and cool your home using electricity, making it a versatile and energy-efficient alternative to traditional air conditioners and furnaces.<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">Think of a heat pump like a refrigerator that can run in reverse. Just as a fridge pulls heat from inside and releases it outside to keep your food cold, a heat pump can pull heat from outside your home and bring it indoors\u2014or push indoor heat outside to cool your home.<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading2\" data-header=\"2\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.94pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.94pt\" data-hd-info=\"2\" data-line-height=\"1.2\"><strong>The Basics: How It Works\u00a0\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">Heat pumps operate on a simple principle: heat exists even in cold air, and it can be moved using a refrigerant cycle. Here&#8217;s how it works in different seasons:<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading3\" data-header=\"3\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.04pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.04pt\" data-hd-info=\"3\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">In Heating Mode (Winter):<span data-range-char-type=\"start\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_delgnbsp57je&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocwb5t3t7udz2a&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_delgnbsp57je\">\u00a0<\/span><span data-range-char-type=\"end\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_delgnbsp57je&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocwb5t3t7udz2a&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_delgnbsp57je\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"16735590\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16735590&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The heat pump extracts heat from the outside air (even when it&#8217;s cold).<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"16735590\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16735590&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The refrigerant absorbs this heat and carries it through a compressor to increase its temperature.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"16735590\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16735590&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Warm refrigerant moves into the indoor coil and releases heat into your home.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"16735590\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16735590&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The refrigerant then cycles back to pick up more heat from outside.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading3\" data-header=\"3\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.04pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.04pt\" data-hd-info=\"3\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">\u2744\ufe0f In Cooling Mode (Summer):<span data-range-char-type=\"start\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_6xiuedtb10ex&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocap5i105r7c1b&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_6xiuedtb10ex\">\u00a0<\/span><span data-range-char-type=\"end\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_6xiuedtb10ex&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocap5i105r7c1b&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_6xiuedtb10ex\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"96541396\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;96541396&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The heat pump pulls heat from inside your home.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"96541396\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;96541396&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">That heat is transferred to the refrigerant and sent outdoors.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"96541396\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;96541396&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The system releases the heat outside, cooling your indoor air.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"96541396\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;96541396&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">The process repeats to maintain your desired indoor temperature.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading2\" data-header=\"2\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.94pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.94pt\" data-hd-info=\"2\" data-line-height=\"1.2\"><strong>Types of Heat Pumps\u00a0\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">There are a few types of heat pumps, but the most common for homes are:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"13767065\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;13767065&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Air-source heat pumps: These absorb and release heat using the air around your home.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"13767065\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;13767065&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Ground-source (or geothermal) heat pumps: These use the more stable temperatures underground to move heat.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"13767065\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;13767065&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Ductless mini-split systems: These offer flexibility for homes without ductwork.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading2\" data-header=\"2\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.94pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.94pt\" data-hd-info=\"2\" data-line-height=\"1.2\"><strong>Why Heat Pumps Are Efficient\u00a0\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-bottom=\"12pt\" data-margin-top=\"12pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">Heat pumps don\u2019t generate heat\u2014they simply move it. This makes them far more efficient than systems that burn fuel or use electric resistance (like space heaters). For every unit of electricity a heat pump uses, it can provide 3\u20134 units of heat, significantly reducing your energy bills and carbon footprint.<\/p>\n<p class=\"zw-paragraph heading2\" data-header=\"2\" data-margin-bottom=\"14.94pt\" data-margin-top=\"14.94pt\" data-hd-info=\"2\" data-line-height=\"1.2\">Benefits of Using a Heat Pump<span data-range-char-type=\"start\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_od6bmg9jl6cc&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocrw83zb0thcxi&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_od6bmg9jl6cc\">\u00a0<\/span><span data-range-char-type=\"end\" data-bookmark-info=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;bookmark&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;toc_od6bmg9jl6cc&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;_Tocrw83zb0thcxi&quot;}\" data-bookmark-id=\"toc_od6bmg9jl6cc\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"51932523\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;51932523&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Energy savings: Lower heating and cooling costs.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"51932523\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;51932523&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">All-in-one comfort: Heating and cooling from one system.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"51932523\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;51932523&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Eco-friendly: Fewer greenhouse gas emissions.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"51932523\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;51932523&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Long-term reliability: Durable and low-maintenance.<\/li>\n<li class=\"zw-list zw-paragraph heading0\" data-header=\"0\" data-textformat=\"{&quot;size&quot;:&quot;12.00&quot;,&quot;fgc&quot;:&quot;rgb(0, 0, 0)&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}\" data-margin-left=\"0.5in\" data-text-indent=\"-0.25in\" data-margin-bottom=\"0pt\" data-hd-info=\"0\" data-line-height=\"1.2\" data-list-id=\"51932523\" data-list-info=\"{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;51932523&quot;,&quot;l&quot;:0}\">Quiet operation: Modern systems run quietly and efficiently.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"energ-after-content\" id=\"energ-1903691935\"><script async src=\"\/\/pagead2.googlesyndication.com\/pagead\/js\/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-4467099352079704\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"><\/script><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:inline-block;width:728px;height:90px;\" \ndata-ad-client=\"ca-pub-4467099352079704\" \ndata-ad-slot=\"8891238828\"><\/ins> \n<script> \n(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); \n<\/script>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>By Ruth Carol Atieno If you&#8217;ve been looking for an energy-efficient way to keep your home warm in the winter and cool in the summer, you may have come across the term heat pump. But what exactly is a heat pump\u2014and how does it work? In this blog, we&#8217;ll break it down in simple terms, [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":3762,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_seopress_robots_primary_cat":"none","_seopress_titles_title":"","_seopress_titles_desc":"But what exactly is a heat pump\u2014and how does it work? In this blog, we'll break it down in simple terms, so you can understand how heat pumps provide comfort all year round while saving energy.","_seopress_robots_index":"","_et_pb_use_builder":"","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":"","_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"categories":[202,197,24,1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-3759","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-advisory","category-energy-financial-calculator","category-energy-industry-news","category-uncategorized"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3759","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3759"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3759\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":3765,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3759\/revisions\/3765"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/3762"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=3759"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=3759"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=3759"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}